00:51:30.165 --> 00:51:31.540
has that property,
that no matter

00:51:31.540 --> 00:51:33.710
what partition--
sequence of partitions

00:51:33.710 --> 00:51:36.280
I take the Riemann
sums converge to I.

00:51:36.280 --> 00:51:39.670
So that's the second
and last thing I need

00:51:39.670 --> 00:51:41.410
to do to prove this theorem.

00:51:44.590 --> 00:52:08.630
So claim-- let x be now any
