00:52:55.600 --> 00:52:56.100
OK?

00:52:56.100 --> 00:52:58.170
This number I is therefore--

00:53:03.272 --> 00:53:05.480
satisfies that property
that, no matter what sequence

00:53:05.480 --> 00:53:10.290
of partitions I
take, the sequence

00:53:10.290 --> 00:53:12.870
of Riemann sums with
respect to these partitions

00:53:12.870 --> 00:53:14.705
converges to that number.

00:53:14.705 --> 00:53:16.080
Of course, here
I'm calling it I,

00:53:16.080 --> 00:53:20.580
but we denoted by the integral
from a, b of f of x dx.

00:53:25.480 --> 00:53:31.620
So to prove this is
not too difficult using

00:53:31.620 --> 00:53:32.830
what we have on the board.

00:53:32.830 --> 00:53:37.800
So remember, I is the limit with
respect to this one sequence

00:53:37.800 --> 00:53:40.200
of partitions, and now we
have an arbitrary sequence

00:53:40.200 --> 00:53:45.120
of partitions, which we want to
show the Riemann sums converge

00:53:45.120 --> 00:53:46.560
to this number as well.

00:53:51.810 --> 00:54:02.760
So with y sub r-- or yr and zeta
r, the partitions from before,

00:54:02.760 --> 00:54:03.330
we have--

00:54:07.550 --> 00:54:13.540
by the triangle
inequality, if I look

00:54:13.540 --> 00:54:26.250
at the Riemann sum with
respect to this arbitrary

00:54:26.250 --> 00:54:27.600
partition now--

00:54:27.600 --> 00:54:30.720
subtract I-- I want to
show this convergence to 0,

00:54:30.720 --> 00:54:33.240
so I'm just going to
bound this by something

00:54:33.240 --> 00:54:34.290
that converges to 0.

00:54:34.290 --> 00:54:37.560
And then, by the usual argument
with the squeeze theorem,

00:54:37.560 --> 00:54:40.710
that implies this
thing converges to 0.

00:54:40.710 --> 00:54:47.270
So adding and subtracting
the Riemann sum associated

00:54:47.270 --> 00:54:50.540
to the partition y and zetas--

00:54:50.540 --> 00:54:59.150
this is less than or equal to
in the triangle inequality,

00:54:59.150 --> 00:55:11.705
minus sf of
[INAUDIBLE] plus now--

00:55:18.050 --> 00:55:20.930
minus I.

00:55:20.930 --> 00:55:23.760
And so I'm almost there.

00:55:23.760 --> 00:55:27.050
This thing now-- I
use theorem three.

00:55:27.050 --> 00:55:28.715
So this is less
than or equal to--

00:55:44.720 --> 00:55:47.600
times b minus a plus--

00:55:56.590 --> 00:56:06.170
s sub f of i sub r minus I. OK?

00:56:16.980 --> 00:56:21.330
The norm of the x sub r--
this is converging to 0.

00:56:21.330 --> 00:56:23.910
So this converges to--

00:56:23.910 --> 00:56:27.780
since the modulus of continuity
goes to 0 as the argument goes

00:56:27.780 --> 00:56:30.750
to 0, this goes to 0, plus--

00:56:30.750 --> 00:56:35.700
remember, the same
